#Lyrics
Upon the cross extended, see, world, thy Lord suspended; thy Savior yields his breath; the Prince of Life from heaven himself hath borne the burden and tasted death.  2. Come, see what is elected; Love's utmost gift perfected, he bleeds upon the tree. The Prince of Life in sorrow, who needs not beg or borrow, dies here for thee.  3. Who can approach this sorrow, whose heart doth not here borrow grief from my Savior's woe? And yet this death so bitter brings life that shall not wither to all below.  4. My guilt, Lord, Thou hast taken; let me not be forsaken; Thou for my sins hast bled. O Jesu, my salvation, my hope and consolation, raise Thou my head.  5. Lord, when I come to dying, upon Thy cross relying, may I find shelter there; and, by Thy death now, living, in mercy be forgiving the cross I bear.

